item.description:
Sticky Footer for Your Website!  Footer at the bottom of page: For your HTML use&hellip;
&lt;body&gt; &lt;div id=&quot;page-container&quot;&gt; &lt;div id=&quot;content-wrap&quot;&gt; &lt;!-- all other page content --&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;footer id=&quot;footer&quot;&gt;&lt;/footer&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;/body&gt;   For CSS an example to use is&hellip;
#page-container { position: relative; min-height: 100vh; } #content-wrap { padding-bottom: 2.5rem; /* Footer height */ } #footer { position: absolute; bottom: 0; width: 100%; height: 2.5rem; /* Footer height */ }  The page-container id tag covers the whole page (header, content, and footer), while the content-wrap id tag covers only the content (and possibly the header if you want to include it) while leaving the footer out so that you can position it in its absolute position to the bottom, hence:  bottom: 0;
